    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Here is how you do it in IntelliJ-IDEA:</p>\n<ol>\n<li><p>Make a run configuration called Remote of the type 'Remove JVM Debug', and attach it to the running service.   This will not start up until your service you want to debug is running and listening on the port (usually 5005).  If you try, it might say it cannot bind to the port 5005.  In the Intellij-IDEA run config setup, it will also suggest to you an optional string of JVM args you can copy to pasted as JVM args to your service.</p>\n</li>\n<li><p>Make a Maven run configuration that runs your app normally.    The maven command should be: <code>package azure-functions:run -DenableDebug</code>\nwhen that starts, it quietly listens on port 5005 (you don't need to run this one with the debug button in intellij. the regular run button will work).   Optionally, instead of -DenableDebug, you can past the debug args you copied from step 1.</p>\n</li>\n<li><p>Start the main service in debug mode</p>\n</li>\n<li><p>Start the Remote debugger run config in Debug mode</p>\n</li>\n<li><p>You might need to click a little grey hyperlink at the top of your service console output to force the service to connect to the debugger.</p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p>It's pretty silly that NOBODY can explain this.  If you Google it, you'll get wierd run-arounds by everyone trying to explain it.</p>\n"
  } ],
